Owner Collaboration for Repurposing or Installation.
a. Major Modifications. Any modification, repurposing, or installation (hereafter, "Major Modification") that results in a change of the Software’s original intended functionality or that involves deploying the Software for public or commercial use must be executed in collaboration with the copyright owner.
b. Prior Approval Requirement. Before making any Major Modification, you must contact the owner at a designated contact point (e.g., email or other means provided by the owner) to discuss your intended changes and secure explicit, written authorization.
c. Non-Collaborative Use. Any use, distribution, or installation of a repurposed version of the Software that has not been approved in writing by the owner is prohibited.
Permissible Modifications.
a. Modifications solely for internal use, experimental purposes, or personal projects that do not lead to public deployment or commercial exploitation are allowed without prior collaboration, provided that such modifications do not alter the fundamental design or intended functionality of the Software.
b. In all cases, if you subsequently decide to distribute or deploy a modified version publicly, you must retroactively secure the owner’s approval as outlined in Section 2.
Distribution Requirements.
a. Any distribution of the Software, whether modified or unmodified, must include a complete copy of this License.
b. In the case of a Major Modification, the distribution must clearly state that the version distributed was subject to collaborative development under this License and include a reference to the correspondence or agreement with the owner (without disclosing any confidential details).
Reservation of Rights.
The owner reserves the right to refuse or withdraw permission for any proposed Major Modification if it is determined that such changes do not align with the original objectives or integrity of the Software. The owner’s decision is final and must be respected by all parties.
